property.name: text
property.value: Vehicle Dynamics State: * Ve - Velocity, earth fixed frame (what the velocity appears to be to an outside observer, i.e., a vehicle heading North-East has its speed split [in an norm sense] between the x and y components) * Ab - Acceleration. * Xe - Position, earth fixed frame. * p,q,r - Angular velocity, body fixed frame. * DCM - Direction cosine matrix, a.k.a. rotation matrix. Rotates a vector between the body frame and the earth fixed frame. * Euler - The Euler angles.

property.name: text
property.value:
This subsystem models a six-degree-of-freedom system in Euler angles. A direct cosine matrix (DCM) is produced to allow for easy transformations to and from the reference frame of the body.
Based on model by: J. Kapinski, CMU Edited by Mankit Leung and Edward A. Lee, Berkeley

property.name: text
property.value: > Ve Velocity, earth fixed frame (what the velocity appears to be to an outside observer, i.e., a vehicle heading North-East has its speed split [in an norm sense] between the x and y components).

property.name: text
property.value: > p,q,r Angular velocity, body fixed frame.

property.name: text
property.value: > pdot, qdot, rdot Angular acceleration, body fixed frame.

property.name: text
property.value: > Vb Velocity, body fixed frame (what the velocity appears to be if you were sitting on the vehicle, i.e., if you're flying straight forward, the first component of this vector, in the x-direction, would be your speed, and the others are zero).

property.name: text
property.value: > DCM Direction cosine matrix, a.k.a. rotation matrix. Rotates a vector between the body frame and the earth fixed frame.

property.name: text
property.value:
> Theta This is the Euler angles (it's wired to the Euler output).
> Omega This is the body fixed angular rates (it's wired to the p,q,r output).

property.name: text
property.value: inertia matrix in body frame, kg m^2
